    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix tracer group on/off functionality not working correctly\n\n### Summary\nThe tracer functionality for enabling/disabling groups of events was not working as expected. When attempting to turn on/off a group of events, the operation would silently fail without any error message.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/database.c`: Added final sorting of groups and IDs arrays after parsing to ensure proper binary search operation\n- The `onoff_group()` function now correctly finds and toggles groups of events\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Start any OAI tracer application (e.g., `enb` or `ue`)\n2. Try to enable a group of events using the group name (e.g., \"LEGACY_GROUP_INFO\")\n3. Observe that the group is not enabled despite no error message being shown\n4. Individual events can still be enabled/disabled, but group operations fail\n\nThe fix ensures that both groups and individual events can be properly toggled on/off through the tracer interface.\n"
}